{
  "_doc": "Phase-4b demo: D-latch and SR-latch — level-sensitive cousins of the flip-flops from 4a. Click VERILOG to see how latches differ from FFs:\n  • Sensitivity is `@(*)` instead of `@(posedge clk)` — latches are level-triggered, transparent while the enable is high.\n  • The body is wrapped in `if (en) begin ... end` — when EN is low, no assignment fires and the reg holds its value.\n  • SR-latch nests a second `if/else` inside the EN gate to pick between set / reset / hold based on (s & ~r) and (~s & r).\nNo CLOCK component is needed for latches — EN takes its place. iverilog parses both without warnings.",
